{{Infobox power station | name = Calasparra Photovoltaic Power Plant | name_official = Planta solar fotovoltaico Calasparra | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Spain | location_map_size = | location_map_caption= | coordinates = {{coord|38.261|-1.681|type:landmark_region:ES|display=inline,title}} | country = Spain | location = [[Calasparra]], [[Region of Murcia|Murcia]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = PV | solar_csp_heliostats= | solar_cpvt = | ps_units_manu_model = | solar_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity= 20 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac= | website = | extra = }} '''Calasparra Photovoltaic Power Plant''' ({{lang-es|Planta solar fotovoltaico Calasparra}}) is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Calasparra]], [[Region of Murcia|Murcia]] in [[Spain]]. The project consists of different production units. Calasparra II is a 6.67&nbsp;MW ground-mounted unit with estimated annual output of 11.82&nbsp;GWh. Calasparra III is a 6.6&nbsp;MW units with estimated annual output of 11.7&nbsp;GWh.<ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=20692 eXenewable Project Profile Page - Calasparra, PV, Spain]</ref> The project was developed by FRV and constructed by Gestamp Solar.
