'''Myristamine oxide''' is an [[amine oxide]] based [[zwitterionic]] [[surfactant]] with a C<sub>14</sub> (tetradecyl) alkyl tail. It is used as a foam stabilizer and hair conditioning agent in some [[shampoo]]s and [[Hair conditioner|conditioners]]. Like other amine oxide based surfactants it is [[antimicrobial]], being slightly more effective than [[lauryldimethylamine oxide]] against the common bacteria ''S. aureus'' and ''E. coli''.<ref name=birnie />
==See also== *[[Lauryldimethylamine oxide]] – An analogous compound with a C<sub>12</sub> tail
