{{Infobox company | name = Nuclearelectrica S.A. | logo = | caption = | type = State owned | traded_as = {{BVB|SNN}} | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|1998}} | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Bucharest]] | location_country = [[Romania]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = Theodor Chirica (CEO) | industry = [[Electricity]] | products = | services = | revenue = US$564&nbsp;million (2007) | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = 2,500 (2007) | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.nuclearelectrica.ro}} | footnotes = | intl = }} ''' Nuclearelectrica ''' is a [[state-owned]] company, its shares being held by the [[Ministry of Economy and Commerce (Romania)|Ministry of Economy and Commerce]], which has as main objective [[power generation]] with the only nuclear power plant in [[Romania]].
''' Nuclearelectrica ''' owns the [[Cernavodă Nuclear Power Plant]] which has 2 reactors and a total installed capacity of 1,411.6 &nbsp;[[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] and an annual average power production of 5.613&nbsp;GWh meaning 19.4% <ref name=wnn2> {{cite news |url=http://www.nuclearelectrica.ro/piata-de-energie/snn-pe-piata-de-energie-electrica-6a436/ |title=Percentage of the total production of electrical energy in Romania |publisher=SN Nuclearelectrica SA |date=2012 |accessdate=2014-03-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130710160210/http://www.nuclearelectrica.ro/piata-de-energie/snn-pe-piata-de-energie-electrica-6a436/ |archivedate=10 July 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>of the total national output of [[Romania]].
The company is also undergoing negotiations for the construction of the 3 and 4 units at [[Cernavodă Nuclear Power Plant]], project expected to cost around US$ 3.5 billion. On 7 March 2008, Nuclearelectrica, [[ArcelorMittal]], [[CEZ Group|CEZ]], [[Electrabel]], [[Enel]], [[Iberdrola]] and [[RWE]] agreed to set up a company dedicated to the completion, commissioning and operation of the units 3 and 4. The company is expected to be registered in May 2008.<ref name=wnn1>{{cite news |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.com/NN/Draft_agreement_finalized_for_Romanian_reactors_070308.html |title= Draft agreement finalized for Romanian reactors | publisher=World Nuclear News |date=2008-03-07 |accessdate=2008-03-07}}</ref>
